node.text:
BSSM pastors and worship teams want to minister to YOU!

You’re invited to a night exclusively for our local church members, to come worship and encounter the heart of God in a special Encounter Room for the Local Church.

During the school year, BSSM regularly hosts live times of prayer and worship streamed on YouTube for both students and the global BSSM family. These times have been presence-filled and powerful! This summer, they are seeking to create space to bless you. The first BSSM Encounter Room for Local Church in May was incredibly impactful. God loves to fill the room when His children show up in worship!

Worship will be led by Hannah Waters and David Funk, with ministry led by BSSM pastors on June 23rd at 6:30-8:00 PM in the College View Sanctuary. If you’re unable to attend, the event will also be publicly streamed to Youtube so you can watch on BSSM’s Youtube channel! (link in bio)
 
We hope to see you there. You won’t want to miss this beautiful time of worship and encountering the love of Jesus!

node.text:
We received a powerful, prophetic word just days before the lockdown began last year. In a season where planning a new campus for our global movement did not seem to make practical sense, we held on to God’s logic and His perfect timing. This was one of the many words from God that we declared over our church and community last year.  

But it is now a new season. We need to be ready for what’s on the horizon. God has confirmed that we need to build now for what is coming tomorrow. God, give us eyes to see and ears to always recognize Your voice! Let’s declare faith-filled prayers as we step into this new chapter together.

Learn more or make a gift at bethel.com/build

node.text: Tune is as John Eldredge and Jason Vallotton talk about what it takes to be a man and our upcoming BraveCo Men’s Conference!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on July 19, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, beard and text that says 'THE QUESTION EVERY MAN ASKS HIMSELF: DO I HAVE WHAT IT TAKES?'.

node.text:
“Until a man knows he's a man, he will forever be trying to prove he is one.” - John Eldridge

From the time a child is born, God’s design was that each boy would hear a thousand times over “you have what it takes to be a man,” from his parents. However, due to a fatherless society and the broken state of families, this question remains painfully unanswered in the hearts of our kids. Consequently, our young boys grow into men who chase women, money, and power in order to satisfy their longing to be known as “manly.” Unfortunately, the pursuit of materialistic objects will never provide the surety that was supposed to be poured into him from birth. 

So, what do you do if your God-given masculinity was never affirmed? For starters, dive into the heart of God and find out how He sees you. Next, find a man that can pour his wisdom and confidence into you. If you’ve had no guide or a bad guide for masculinity throughout your life, it may be time to find a new one. 

The truth is, discovering masculinity and walking it out is a lifelong journey of exploration with God, and other men, as you unearth the capabilities, power, and strength God has already placed within you. 

You will never know that you have what it takes if you are bound by the fear that you won’t. Afraid to jump in? Remember that failing forward gives us room for trial and error, research, and development, and it builds confidence in yourself.

We believe that you have what it takes, and we want you to believe that too.

BraveCo is a movement of men that are not afraid to get in the foxhole together, take risks and fail forward, and step into our greatest potential. If you’re hungry to understand true masculinity and walk boldly in your God-given manhood, we invite you to join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference with speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, and Jason Vallotton.

Aug 25 - Aug 27, 2021. Register now at bethel.ws/braveco

Join us tonight, July 19, at 6pm PST to hear LIVE from John Eldredge and Jason Vallotton on Instagram!

node.text: "Lord, You know everything there is to know about me. You perceive every movement of my heart and soul, and You understand my every thought before it even enters my mind. You are so intimately aware of me, Lord. You read my heart like an open book and You know all the words I’m about to speak before I even start a sentence! You know every step I will take before my journey even begins. You’ve gone into my future to prepare the way, and in kindness You follow behind me to spare me from the harm of my past. You have laid Your hand on me! This is just too wonderful, deep, and incomprehensible! Your understanding of me brings me wonder and strength." - Psalm 139:1-6, TPT

node.text: We're praying for you, that God would equip you with strength, wisdom, and courage to know how to partner with heaven and see breakthrough in your life and the lives of your family.

node.text: Happy 70th Birthday, Pastor Bill! We're so incredibly thankful for you. The many yeses that you've given to God throughout the years have shaped and formed so much of who we are as a community and as a movement. May this year be filled with abundant blessing, deep hope, continued breakthroughs, and powerful encounters with God! We love you!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on July 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'GUILT AND SHAME WON'T GIVE YOU ACCESS TO WHAT HUMILITY DOES. BILL JOHNSON'.

node.text: When God reveals that there are things within us personally that cannot stay, we are invited to respond with humility, which is not the same as guilt or shame. God, let us be people who are full of wisdom to recognize when You are bringing something to the surface for us to deal with. Help us to respond with humility, and deal with the issue with You, in its entirety and without hesitation.

node.text: There's something so powerful about shared moments in worship as a community. Spiritual history is built with one another as we lift our voices and focus our hearts on the One who calls us His children. Whether in living rooms or in church buildings, outside at a park or around a bonfire, take time to share these moments with your community!

node.text:
The Lamb of God is fully alive and well in the Church, but in many places, the Lion has been declawed. Some of us welcome the Jesus who was kind and gentle enough to make friends with little children, yet we reject the Jesus who built a whip before He turned tables over in the temple. 

In the same way, the Church wants kind boys, but does not always make room for powerful, free men. We love the idea that man is made in the image of God, especially the Lamb that was slain. In fact, in many places you can be whatever you want as long as it doesn’t resemble the Lion who brings raw strength and power that tramples any foe beneath His feet. 

The truth is, if we miss the masculine heart of God, we also miss the masculine heart of man. 
Men—true masculinity was built into your DNA—yet it has been blurred by the many conflicting messages we've received from the world around us, whether by the Church or by society.

The Word of the Lord says God created man in His own image and called it good. God created a clear, powerful purpose for manhood. The world, our families, and other men miss out when we do not arise and fulfill our original design. 

If you’re hungry to understand your masculinity and walk boldly in your God-given manhood, we invite you to join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference with speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, and Jason Vallotton. 

Aug 25 - Aug 27, 2021. Register now at bethel.ws/braveco

Never attended BSSM (but always wanted to)? This is for you!

We want to minister to you! Join Kris Vallotton and BSSM Pastors for BSSM Online Open House, a free Zoom event open to the public.

July 13, 2021, from 3:30-5:30 PM join us for our BSSM Online Open House as we hear from, Kris Vallotton @kvministries, BSSM Co-Founder, followed by a time of ministry with the BSSM Online team. You will also get to experience what it is like to be plugged into our Revival Groups, where students break out into smaller groups led by BSSM Pastors.

Come and experience a taste of what BSSM Online is like and receive a fresh touch from the Lord. These times in the past have been so refreshing and hope-filled, and we know that this time will be no different!

This is an exclusive event with limited seats, so make sure that you register at  bethel.ws/openhousesignup. Can’t wait to see you there!
